ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: (Hypomania) Have there been times when you felt very happy indeed without a break for days on end?
(Hypomania) Was there an obvious reason for this? (you felt very happy indeed without a break for days on end)
(Hypomania) Did your relatives or friends think it was strange or complain about it? (you felt very happy indeed without a break for days on end)
(Hypomania) During this happy period, did you find you were getting on with far more things than usual without getting tired, so that you needed little sleep?
(Hypomania) Did this occur over the past year?
(Insertion) Have you ever felt that your thoughts were directly interfered with or controlled by some outside force or person?
(Insertion) Did this come about in a way that many people would find hard to believe, for instance, through telepathy?
(Insertion) Was it just because people were going out of their way to be persuasive?
(Insertion) Was it just because people were distracting you?
(Insertion) Did this occur over the past year?
(Paranoia) Have there been times when you felt that people were against you?
(Paranoia) Have there been times when you felt that people were deliberately acting to harm you or your interests?
(Paranoia) Have there been times when you felt that a group of people was plotting to cause you serious harm or injury?
(Paranoia) Did this occur over the past year?
(Abnormal) Have you there been times when things looked or sounded or felt abnormal to you?
(Abnormal) Have there been times when you felt things changed their appreance while you looked at them?
(Abnormal) Have there been times when things changed in size or shape while you looked at them?
(Abnormal) Did this occur over the past year?
(Strange Exp.) Have there been times when you felt that something strange was going on?
(Strange Exp.) Did you feel it was so strange that other people would find it very hard to believe? (you felt that something strange was going on)
(Strange Exp.) Did you feel it was so strange that you yourself could not explain it? (you felt that something strange was going on)
(Strange Exp.) Did this occur over the past year?
(Hallucination) Have there been times when you heard or saw things that other people could not?
(Hallucination) Did you at any time hear voices saying quite a few words or sentences when there was no-one around that might account for it?
(Hallucination) Did you at any time see visions?
(Hallucination) Did this occur over the past year?
